FBIS4-38722 "drsov106_b_94008" FBIS-SOV-94-106 Daily Report 1 Jun 1994 RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS Economic Issues Chernomyrdin To Continue Working on Economic Edicts Chernomyrdin To Continue Working on Economic Edicts LD0106134794 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1301 GMT 1 Jun 94 LD0106134794 Moscow ITAR-TASS English BFN [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Gennadiy Yezhov] [Text] Moscow June 1 TASS -- Russian Prime Minister Viktor Chernomyrdin vacationing on the Black Sea will continue working on the second package of economic decrees which is now being drawn up by the government, governmental spokesman Valeriy Grishin said on Wednesday. Grishin said that first vice-prime minister Oleg Soskovets will substitute for the premier for the duration of his two-week vacation which he will spend in the Black Sea resort city of Sochi. The spokesman said that until the last minute it was not clear whether or not Chernomyrdin will take his leave now, mainly because of his active involvement in the work on the package of economic decrees aimed at continuing economic reforms in russia. The first package was recently signed by president Boris Yeltsin. Grishin denied reports that Chernomyrdin would work on his book during his vacation. "There will be simply no time left for that. Besides, he needs rest too," he said.
